      "excerptOrSummary": "AC1: independently reproduced end-to-end with a hand-built fixture distinct from the shipped eval -- a durable assignment record held by successor-actor-iter3-stable with a fresh liveness heartbeat (fresh_liveness_heartbeat, durable-conflict path). verify-hold as a STABLE, differing FLOW_AGENTS_ACTOR (original-zombie-actor-A-iter3) returns exit 1/ok:false/held; publish-delivery as that same zombie actor exits 1, REFUSING to publish, delivery/ never created; the true fresh holder succeeds on the identical fixture as a control (exit 0, delivery/ created). A separate reclaimable fixture (stale ~90-day assignment, no liveness) re-checked by a different STABLE actor still returns exit 1/ok:false/reclaimable. Zombie protection is completely unaffected by the SECOND CI-blocking fix because it only ever changes behavior for an UNSTABLE (ancestry/unresolved) actor identity.",
